description.author: Sam May
description.synopsis: An implementation of the web Document Object Model, and its rendering.
description.description:
`willow` is the basis of a web browser suite, providing the
underlying types to represent various documents found on
the internet.  It does /not/ provide parsing algorithms for
anything but the simplest filetypes, instead expecting them
to be outsourced to other modules.

package-flags.name: html5lib
package-flags.description:
Enable the html5lib tests, which require manually
downloading the test data.

package-flags.name: wpt
package-flags.description:
Enable integration with web-platform-tests suite, greatly
expanding the test surface at the expense of requiring the
manual download of the (large) test data repository.
